BBC Later with Jools Holland S49E01 1080i HDTV h264-NX

Later... With Jools Holland returns for its 49th series with the sort of exclusives that makes it the key taste-making destination in music television. Kings of Leon return with their first album in three years, Walls, which finds them re-energised and returning to the anthemic sound and classic songwriting of their best work. Jack White has appeared on the show with the White Stripes, The Raconteurs and Dead Weather, but now he makes his solo acoustic debut, re-interpreting songs from his back catalogue. Sting has sold over 100 million albums and has been touring the past two years with both Paul Simon and Peter Gabriel, but he has also found time to make his first straight-ahead rock 'n' roll album in many a year. Stir into that the dark R&B of LA's Banks and Antibes-grown LA-based Frenchman Anthony Gonzalez's band M83.
